== /z/ phoneme in Telugu ==
The word for true is "nizame." The romanization I just typed is exactly how it sounds in Telugu. The problem is that the IPA for it is incorrect. /nid͡ʒaːme/ should actually be /nizəːme/ otherwise the romanization would've been "nijaame". It seems like someone just transliterated the Telugu script into IPA and paid no attention to pronunciation, because the script uses /d͡ʒ/ to represent /z/ like Devnagri. Of course, this could be different from my Gunturi dialect. I am going to go ahead and change it. [[User:Xerces1492|Xerces1492]] ([[User talk:Xerces1492|discuss]] • [[Special:Contributions/Xerces1492|contribs]]) 21:39, 19 January 2013 (UTC)

